    <p>The "Web Vitals" Chrome extension, a fork of Web Vitals, collects the following data:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Performance Metrics:</strong> Metrics such as Largest Contentful Paint (LCP), First Input Delay (FID), and Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) from the web pages you visit.</li>
      <li><strong>Temporary URLs:</strong> URLs of visited pages may be temporarily stored during analysis to measure performance but are not retained afterward.</li>
      <li><strong>No Personal Data:</strong> The extension does not collect personally identifiable information (PII) such as your name, email, or browsing history beyond what is needed for performance analysis.</li>
